Introduction

HIGHTEEN (Korean: 하이틴; Japanese: ハイティーン; also stylized as HighTeen) was a four-member girl group under Illusion Entertainment. They released the pre-debut single "Grow Up" on May 25, 2016 and officially debuted on October 14, 2016 with the mini-album Teen Magic. They presumably disbanded during late 2019 since their SNS has been inactive since August.
